            <h3>Isabela City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>1. Revel in the Cocowayan Festival, a week-long celebration in line with the City’s founding anniversary marked with fes- tive street dancing, colorful parade, sports activities, fairs, cultural and variety shows and beauty pageant.</li>
                <li>2. Discover and enjoy the scenery of the unspoiled beaches like the white sands of the Malamawi beach. Enjoy trekking on the nearby mountain trails and see the panoramic view of Isabela Channel once one gets to the top.</li>
                <li>3. Shop and savor the cheap and freshest variety of seafood and fruits.</li>
                <li>4. Enjoy the City’s fiesta on July 8 in honor of Sta. Isabel de Portugal. Experience Isabeleños charm and warm hospitality.</li>
                <li>5. Tour around the City’s picturesque landscape and rubber plantation. Explore the forest grounds of the City at Maligue Nursery and enjoy the clean and fresh air brought about by the tall trees that gives the feeling of being one with Mother Nature.</li>
            </ol>
