            <h4>How to get there</h4>
            <p>Visiting Isabela City is made possible by sea travel via Zam- boanga City. There are five trips plying the Zamboanga-Isa- bela channel. It takes about 45 minutes via fast craft and an average of one hour and twenty minutes for regular ferries.</p>
            <p>In the urban areas, constituents and transients ride motor- ized tricycles. In the mountainous barangays, public utility jeepneys convey passengers and goods going in and out of the City proper.</p>
